 Randomized Control Trial.

.

 A randomized controlled trial in which pregnant women undergoing a scheduled Elective cesarean delivery were assigned to skin closure with surgical staples and were randomly assigned to the day of removal of surgical staples.

 Postoperative day 4 VS.

 Postoperative day 8 .

 Outcome assessors were blinded to group allocation.

 Scars will be evaluated after 8 weeks.

 Primary outcome measures is Patient and Observer Scar Assessment Scale (POSAS) scores.

 Secondary outcome measures are complications of surgical site infection (SSI) or wound disruption (hematoma or seroma).

 A group of 104 women is needed in order to achieve a clinically significant effect with a power of 80%.

